+
+/*
+ * RISC-V RVV 1.0 backend include router. Translated from impl_arm_sve.h.
+ *
+ * RVV support is implemented via the RVV C intrinsics (spec v1.0, __riscv_-
+ * prefixed forms). Like SVE, RVV vectors are natively sizeless (vfloat32m1_t
+ * etc.), which does not fit GROMACS's requirement to know the vector width at
+ * CMake time. GCC 14+ provides -mrvv-vector-bits=zvl, and the
+ * __attribute__((riscv_rvv_vector_bits(N))) type attribute fixes the width, so
+ * we use fixed-size RVV types the same way the SVE backend uses
+ * arm_sve_vector_bits(...). Confirmed on the SpaceMiT X60 at VLEN=256
+ * (kickoff sec.6 probe 1: sizeof(fixed vfloat32m1_t)==32).
+ *
+ * Milestone 1 ships float32 only. The double, simd4, and util (gather/scatter/
+ * transpose) headers are added in later phases; their #includes are commented
+ * out until those files exist so the M1 build configures cleanly.
+ */
+
